**Bento**

**How to think about a bento**

Classic Japanese ratio is roughly **4:3:2:1** вҖ” rice : protein : vegetables : pickle/condiment. Western-style bento is looser, often more like **1/2 veg, 1/4 protein, 1/4 carb**. Both work. The key for prep-ahead is choosing components that hold up at room temperature for 4вҖ“6 hours and don't bleed into each other вҖ” which is why bento boxes have compartments.

A useful mental model: pick **one anchor protein**, **one carb**, **two veg/salad components**, and **one or two small extras** (pickle, egg, fruit, something crunchy). Mix and match from a component library rather than building each box from scratch.

**Component library**

**Anchor proteins (****вҳ…**** = omega-3-strong)**

- вҳ… Teriyaki salmon (cold or room temp, both work)

- вҳ… Miso-glazed salmon or mackerel

- вҳ… Salmon or tuna onigiri (rice ball with fish centre)

- вҳ… Smoked mackerel flaked with lemon

- вҳ… Sardines вҖ” Spanish-style with olive oil, or Japanese-style with ginger

- вҳ… Hot-smoked trout

- вҳ… Tamagoyaki (rolled Japanese omelette) with pasture-raised eggs

- вҳ… Prawns вҖ” poached, or with sesame-tamari

- Cold roast pasture-raised chicken, sliced

- Chicken katsu (homemade, rapeseed oil) вҖ” sliced cold

- Chicken teriyaki

- Korean-style bulgogi beef (grass-fed)

- Char siu pork

- Soy-marinated boiled eggs (ajitsuke tamago)

- Chickpea or white bean salad (Jane, non-fish days)

- Tofu вҖ” sesame-crusted, teriyaki, or marinated

**Carbs**

- Sushi rice (seasoned with rice vinegar вҖ” keeps better than plain)

- Brown rice or short-grain mixed

- Soba noodles, dressed

- Rice noodles with sesame

- Sushi rice with furikake sprinkle (вҳ… if it contains bonito or seaweed)

- Onigiri вҖ” plain, umeboshi, salmon вҳ…, or seaweed-wrapped

- Small portion of seeded sourdough (Western-style bento)

**Veg / salad components**

- Edamame with sea salt

- Sesame spinach (gomae)

- Quick-pickled cucumber with rice vinegar

- Carrot & daikon pickle (namasu)

- Roasted broccoli with sesame

- Blanched green beans with miso-walnut dressing вҳ…

- Cherry tomatoes

- Avocado slices (with lemon to stop browning)

- Roasted squash or sweet potato cubes

- Sugar snap peas

- Wakame seaweed salad вҳ…

- Kimchi (small portion)

- Quick-pickled red cabbage

**Small extras**

- Umeboshi (pickled plum) вҖ” traditional bento centrepiece

- Furikake sprinkle on rice

- Toasted sesame seeds

- A few walnuts вҳ…

- Boiled quail eggs or half a regular egg

- Fresh fruit вҖ” strawberries, grapes, satsuma segments, blueberries

- Pickled ginger

- Nori sheets or strips вҳ…

**Six worked examples**

- **1. Classic salmon bento ****вҳ…** Teriyaki salmon В· sushi rice with black sesame В· sesame spinach В· quick-pickled cucumber В· half a soy egg В· strawberries

- **2. Mackerel ****&**** soba ****вҳ…** Cold smoked mackerel with lemon В· soba noodles dressed in tamari-ginger В· edamame В· pickled carrot В· wakame salad

- **3. Sardine Mediterranean (Western-style) ****вҳ…** Sardines in olive oil on a small bed of rocket В· seeded sourdough В· butter bean salad with parsley and lemon В· cherry tomatoes В· olives В· grapes

- **4. Chicken ****&**** rice (no fish day)** Cold roast chicken with sesame-tamari В· brown rice with furikake В· sesame broccoli В· pickled red cabbage В· cucumber sticks В· satsuma segments

- **5. Tamagoyaki ****&**** onigiri ****вҳ…** Rolled omelette В· two onigiri (one salmon вҳ…, one umeboshi) В· blanched green beans with miso-walnut dressing В· wakame В· blueberries

- **6. Jane veggie bento** White bean & herb salad with olive oil В· sushi rice with furikake В· sesame spinach В· roasted squash cubes В· half a soy egg В· walnuts В· grapes

**Practical notes for prep**

- **Cook rice the night before** вҖ” it actually holds better at room temp than fresh hot rice (food safety: cool quickly, fridge overnight, pack cold)

- **Tamagoyaki and soy eggs** keep 3вҖ“4 days in the fridge, so batch on a Sunday

- **Pickles** keep for weeks вҖ” make a jar of cucumber and a jar of carrot/daikon and you're set

- **Salmon and mackerel** can be cooked in batches and portioned; both are fine cold

- **Onigiri** are best made fresh the night before, wrapped individually in cling film

- **Boxes**: traditional lacquered bento, Monbento, or Sistema-style with compartments all work. Insulated ones extend the safe window if no fridge access

**Other Formats**

- **Mason jar salads** вҖ” layered with dressing at the bottom, hardy veg next, then grains/protein, then leaves on top. Shake when ready to eat. Keeps 4вҖ“5 days in the fridge because the leaves don't touch the dressing. Brilliant for batch prep on a Sunday.

- **Buddha bowls / poke bowls** вҖ” built on the same principle as bento but in a single bowl. Poke specifically is a strong omega-3 play: raw or seared salmon/tuna, sushi rice, edamame, avocado, seaweed, sesame. Travels well in a sealed bowl.

- **Stuffed flatbreads** вҖ” gГ¶zleme (Turkish), msemen (Moroccan), or stuffed paratha. Made ahead, eaten cold or briefly reheated. Spinach and feta-alternative, spiced lamb, or tuna and herb fillings all work.

- **Savoury pancakes** вҖ” Korean pajeon (with prawns вҳ…), Japanese okonomiyaki, or French galettes (buckwheat, naturally). Hold up well, eat at room temp.

- **Stuffed vegetables eaten cold** вҖ” Greek gemista (rice-stuffed tomatoes and peppers), Middle Eastern stuffed vine leaves (dolma), stuffed courgettes. Traditionally served at room temperature, batch beautifully.

- **Terrines and pГўtГ©s** вҖ” smoked mackerel pГўtГ© вҳ… on rye, chicken liver parfait, vegetable terrine. Slice and pack with crackers/bread and pickles. Very French lunch energy.

- **Cold pies and tarts** вҖ” proper quiche (with good eggs), tortilla espaГұola variations, frittata "cake" with layered fillings, smoked salmon and leek tart вҳ…. These are bigger commitments but cut into multiple lunches.

- **Grain-free options** вҖ” cauliflower rice bowls, courgette noodle salads, lettuce wraps. Useful if either of you wants to vary carb load.

**Other ****Cuisines**

- **Korean** вҖ” beyond bibimbap, there's gimbap (Korean rice rolls, often with tuna вҳ…), Korean-style cold noodles (naengmyeon), and a whole world of banchan (small side dishes) that work like bento components.

- **Levantine / Middle Eastern** вҖ” mezze-style boxes are essentially bento with hummus, baba ganoush, tabbouleh, fattoush, kibbeh, falafel (homemade), labneh-alternatives, olives, flatbread. Naturally portioned and travel-friendly.

- **Scandinavian** вҖ” smГёrrebrГёd (open sandwiches on rye) is a strong format for omega-3: gravadlax вҳ…, pickled herring вҳ…, smoked mackerel вҳ…, egg and anchovy вҳ…. Plus Swedish-style cold potato salads with dill.

- **Filipino / Indonesian** вҖ” nasi goreng or nasi lemak boxes, with sambal, peanuts (or swap for cashews), boiled egg, fried fish.

- **Persian** вҖ” kuku sabzi (herb-heavy frittata) is a bento-friendly powerhouse, plus saffron rice with barberries and nuts, and Persian salads.

**Additional ****Component ideas**

- **Better mayo and dressing alternatives** вҖ” homemade aioli (olive oil), tahini-lemon, miso-walnut вҳ…, anchovy vinaigrette вҳ…, salsa verde with anchovies вҳ…, Greek-style yoghurt dressings (Mike), avocado-based dressings.

- **Fermented additions** вҖ” sauerkraut, kimchi, pickled vegetables, miso pastes. Gut health bonus, and they make plain rice/grain bowls more interesting.

- **Seaweed beyond nori** вҖ” wakame, hijiki, dulse flakes as a salt substitute. All omega-3 and iodine wins.

- **Bone broth** вҖ” plain or as a soup base in a thermos. Different nutritional angle (collagen, minerals) that fits a "health regime" frame even if it's not directly a ratio play.

- **Better snacks-as-lunch-components** вҖ” biltong (grass-fed, no seed oils unlike most jerky), good olives, marinated artichokes, anchovy-stuffed peppers, soft-boiled eggs with dukkah.